records.addlTxt:
Defendant Seth M. Kawlewski in court with attorney Melissa Hope Dalkert. Louis John Molepske appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
8:47 a.m.  Court calls the case. 

Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed.
State files Amended Information.  Count 2 is amended to Battery/Domestic Related.
Prosecutor states plea agreement.
Attorney for Defendant concurs with agreement stated.  States one correction re: the fine. 
Atty Molepske makes additional statements. Concurs with the correction. 

Atty Dalkert and the defendant have received a copy of the Amended Information and waive's its reading.  

Defendant enters a plea of: Counts 1 thru 3 - NO CONTEST

Court questions Defendant regarding plea.
Court informs Defendant of Constitutional Rights. Court advises Defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge.
Court questions Attorney for Defendant.
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge(s).

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge(s).
Court finds the defendant guilty Counts 1 thru 3. Clerk directed to enter Judgment of Conviction this date.

Victim is present and makes a statement to the Court. 
Atty Molepske makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Atty Dalkert makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 

BY THE COURT:
Counts 1 & 2 -
Serve 180 days jail, concurrent with each other - STAYED -

Count 3 -
Serve 90 days jail, concurrent with Counts 1 & 2 - STAYED - 

Placed on probation for 36 months: 
Serve 30 days jail. 
Huber for work, counseling and any other reason the sheriff will allow. 
Allowed to serve the entire sentence on Electronic Monitor if he qualifies after being assessed by jail staff. 
2 days credit. 
Sentence to commence within 60 days. 
Must report today for start date. 
Do not possess or consume alcohol.
No contact with Olivia Kizewski except for letter of apology to be written within next 30 days and provide to his agent. 
Maintain fulltime employment. 
Participate in any assessment or counseling recommended by the agent and that can include the Domestic Abuse Alternative Program if available and agent recommends. 
Comply with counseling recommended by Mr. Deets. 
Not possess any dangerous weapons. 
Submit DNA sample. 
Pay costs including the Domestic Abuse Surcharge and DNA surcharge on all 3 counts. Pay during the period of conditions.

State files Information.
Defendant received copy of information.
Defendant waives reading of information. 

NOT GUILTY Plea(s) entered.

Bond Continued.

3:29 pm Defendant Seth M. Kawlewski in court with attorney Melissa H. Dalkert. Louis J. Molepske appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  DA Molepske calls witness, Officer Alan Marchel, who is sworn in and testifies during direct exam.  Witness identifies Defendant in the courtroom. 
3:31 pm Atty Dalkert cross exam.
3:34 pm BTC:   BY THE COURT: Court finds it is probable that a felony was committed and this defendant committed it and binds the defendant over for trial.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for November 23, 2015 at 09:30 am.

Defendant Seth M. Kawlewski in court with attorney Melissa H. Dalkert. Cass W Cousins appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant/Attorney received copy of Criminal Complaint and waived its reading.
Court informs Defendant of Charges and maximum penalties.
Waive time limits.
Bond continued.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for November 16, 2015 at 03:00 pm.

Defendant Seth M. Kawlewski in court. Cass W Cousins appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Court questions the defendant. 
Attorney/Defendant received copy of criminal complaint.
Court informs defendant of charges and maximum penalties.
Attorney/Defendant waives reading of complaint.

Court advises defendant of right to counsel/Public Defender representation.
Defendant indicates he was denied by the public defender and court appointed.  Has spoken to another attorney. 

Court will adjourn to allow to hire counsel.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for November 2, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
